frus:attachment.p:
And whereas, by Article VII of the said treaty, it was further agreed as follows:
If the determination of the foregoing questions as to the exclusive jurisdiction of the United States shall leave the subject in such position that the concurrence of Great Britain is necessary to the establishment of regulations for the proper protection and preservation of the fur seal in or habitually resorting to the Bering £ea, the arbitrators shall then determine what concurrent regulations, outside the jurisdictional limits of the respective Governments, are necessary, and over what waters such regulations should extend;
The high contracting parties furthermore agree to cooperate in securing the adhesion of other powers to such regulations;
